'''G2ZT''' is a [[tetrazole|bistetrazole]].  It is an explosive approximately as powerful as [[RDX]], but it releases less toxic reaction products when detonated: [[ammonia]] and [[hydrogen cyanide]].  When combined with [[ammonium dinitramide|ADN]] or [[ammonium nitrate|AN]] oxidizers, the amount of [[hydrogen cyanide|HCN]] produced by a deflagration may be reduced.  The compound is thus considered by its advocates to be an [[environmentally friendlier]] explosive than traditional [[nitroamine|nitroamine-based]] explosives.<ref>Choi, Charles. "[http://www.livescience.com/technology/080527-friendly-bombs.html Environmentally Friendly Bombs Planned]", Live Science, May 27, 2008.</ref>

'''G2ZT''' is otherwise known as bis(3,4,5-triamino-1,2,4-triazolium) 5,5'-azotetrazolate.

