{{refimprove|date=August 2010}}
The '''Minnedosa Ethanol Plant''' is an [[ethanol]] plant located in [[Minnedosa, Manitoba|Minnedosa]], [[Manitoba]]. The plant is owned by [[Husky Energy]] and produces 130 million litres of [[ethanol]] per year. In Canada, ethanol is blended into gasoline. The plant feedstock for the facility is non-food feed-grade wheat purchased from local growers. However, the plant is also capable of using corn as a feed-stock. The feed-stock is milled, cooked, fermented, distilled and dehydrated resulting in ethanol fuel and the remaining waste material is processed into a high protein feed 
supplement.<ref>[http://www.huskyenergy.com/downloads/abouthusky/publications/factsheets/FS_2009_Ethanol.pdf Plant Overview ]</ref>

The new plant came on line in 2008 replacing an older plant on the site that from 1981 had produced 10 million litres of ethanol 
annually.<ref>[http://www.huskyenergy.com/downloads/newsreleases/2008/HSE_042508_Minnedosa_Opening.pdf Plant comes online]</ref>  The plant was constructed by [[PCL Construction|PCL Industrial Constructors]] <ref>[http://industrial.pcl.com/projects/Active/1500535/index.aspx PCL Overview of Project ]</ref>

