[[File:Sledge 2.JPG|thumb|Sledge 2]] [[File:Ox-drawn sledge in the NWT.jpg|thumb|Ox-drawn sledge carrying firewood.]] [[File:A Sledge with Pipe of Madeira Wine, MON 1909.jpg|thumb|A Sledge with Pipe of Madeira Wine, MON 1909]] A '''stone-boat''' is a type of [[sled]] (sledge) for moving heavy objects<ref>Oxford English Dictionary, 2nd ed, Stone-boat</ref> such as [[Rock (geology)|stone]]s or [[hay]] [[baler|bales]]. Originally they were for [[animal-powered transport]] used with [[horse]]s or [[oxen]] to clear fields of stones and other uses and may still be used with animals or [[tractor]]s today .<ref>[http://www.lilligren.com/homestead/stoneboat.htm A Cheap Alternative Method for Moving Large Round Bales]</ref>
The device may look like a low-profile sled with timber runners or have a flat bottom of planks secured together to slide over soft ground or snow. Originally made of [[wood]], [[metal]] versions exist with hinges.
